item.title: Poles at the Polls
item.author: Piotr Faba,Rajat Jain,
item.description: A radical libertarian party could hold the key to power in Poland after Sunday, when the EU’s sixth largest economy and only country to not contract in 2009 held parliamentary elections. Unsurprisingly, the incumbent centrist PM came out on top; Donald Tusk’s Civic Platform won 39.2% – a slight …
